        "title": "Can there be &#39;var&#39; keyword in Java?",
        "body": "<p>My question can seem stupid... to me it really seems stupid. \nBut I was shocked to see <code>var<\/code> keyword in a java code in video tutorial about android, <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_q9lorDZn0Y\" rel=\"nofollow\">you can see it here, on 38 minute for example...<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>So my question is, how it is possible to have <code>var<\/code> in java code and what does it mean in java, where we cannot have references without specific type? <\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 28303925,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "android"
        ],
        "score": 0,
        "accepted_answer_id": 28303954,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 7217
